                             'PyramiSol' 1.2

                           by Charles-N. Jacob

  'PyramiSol' is a solitaire type of @{" game " link play}, gameplay is the same
as that of 'Tri-Peaks', 'Golf' or other similar games. In this game,
the board consists of 28 cards that are placed in a triangular, or
pyramidal, shape. A card (the 'next' card), facing up is shown at
the bottom under the game board. At the left of that card is a pack
of the remaining cards and that pack is face down. A number
indicates how many cards are remaining in that pack.

  The goal of the game is to empty all the game board by clicking
on cards that are higher or lower by one unit than the 'next card'
in the bottom of the window. For example, if the card is a 7 of
Heart, the choosen card should be a 6 or 8, the colour or type of
figure has no importance.

  Have fun!

