@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "PyramiSol" where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files
or Libraries are needed. The only requirement is that your Workbench
must have at least 8 colours.

                             How to play?

  To play, simply click on a card higher or lower by one unit than
the card shown under the game board (the 'next' card). For example,
if the card is a 7 of Heart, the choosen card must be a 6 or an 8,
whatever the colour or type of figure. Note that in 'PyramiSol' a
King can follow an ace or vice versa.

  You can only choose a card that is entirely shown (a card that is
not hidden in part by another). If a valid card is clicked on, it
is removed from the board and it is placed at the bottom of the
game window, making it the 'next' card.

  When there are no cards that can follow the 'next' card, click on
the remaining cards pack to pick a new card, that card becomes the
'next' card. If the pack is empty and there are no cards that can
follow the 'next' card, the game is over.

  Scoring goes like the following: every time you click on a card
on the board and that card is put on the 'next' card pile, you will
get one point to which will be added one point multiplied by the
number of consecutively completed game boards. When you clear an
entire board and there are face down cards remaining, you will get
a bonus of 10 points multiplied by the number of cards remaining in
that pack, that total will then be multiplied by the number of
consecutively completed game boards.

  You can quit the game by clicking on the main window's closebutton
or by pressing on the 'Esc' key.



  Have fun!

